Course is designed for total beginners. Student will learn to read simple texts, to understand and use simple language and the basic structures of Russian grammar. The given grammar will have practical conversational orientation. Thus a student will be able to build up conversational formulas and develop basic speech habits.

The topics of the course (content of the course might slightly change depending on students' progress):

   Introducing oneself,
   Colours and adjectives,
   Countries, nationalities and languages,
   Family and friends,
   Professions and occupations,
   Numerals, phone numbers, addresses,
   Studies,
   Daily routine,
   Favourite things to do,
   Leisure time and hobbies.

The course focuses on the following grammatical topics: the gender of nouns and adjectives, all cases in singular, personal and possessive pronouns, verb conjugation in present, past and future (imperfective verbs).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The overall aim of the course is to provide a learner with basic knowledge of Russian and help to develop reading as well as basic oral and writing skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course a student should be able to:
- read, write and understand simple texts in Russian;
- express oneself choosing the correct vocabulary and grammar learnt during the course;
- get into social contact (to greet, to say goodbye, to introduce oneself, to thank, to apologies etc.);
- talk about family, home town, hobbies, daily routine;  
- understand and apply basic structures of Russian grammar.
